{
  "stem": "1775.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "They told you again what they wanted you should give them, a certain amount of money, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And the Jewish Judenrat always gave it to them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And it was quiet for a little bit.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "Because I think this was-- the ghetto time from, from January, 1943, until May, it, it, it was quiet, quieter than, than in a long, long time.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "They took all the people from the-- the people that worked by the bristle company, and they told the people that they're going to transfer all the factories, all the places that they were working in, they were going to transfer to Trawniki.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "Trawniki was a place close to Majdanek.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "It was like a suburb of Majdanek, one of those places.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And they took all-- and I think about close to a thousand people, about 800 and something or maybe a little less or more-- I don't know exactly how many-- went with them to work there at Trawniki.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "That was the bristle company.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And afterwards, we still worked in the Ortskommandatur for the Wehrmacht, for the gendarmerie.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "Wherever they, they needed you, they used to send you to work.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And a lot of times, I worked at where people were-- we were sorting clothes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "We were taking all the Jewish clothes, packing, packing them up.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And they were sending it to Germany.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "So a lot of the times, I used to work there during the winter, '43.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "Then in May, it started out again.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "May-- the, the 2nd of May, they took the-- they took-- the German soldiers, the SS, the Ukrainians--a lot of Ukrainians used to be at the actions.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "Wherever they used to kill the Jews, the Ukrainians and the [NON-ENGLISH] and the Lithuanians, they were right there with the Germans.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
